        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/96bed5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-02T22:21:45.778Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal is characterized by being a minimalist and elegant app in terms of design; perhaps with some changes it could look even more perfect and simple. Personally, I love the icons; they are perfectly harmonious and elegant, the color palette is ideal, it doesnâ€™t strain the eyes, and yes, each app is designed based on the intended ecosystem. Overall, itâ€™s great just as it is, although I would like them to move the profile picture icon and its function to the bottom bar on Android, have the global search option like in Messenger, and replace the name of the Signal app with Chats on the main screen like in iOS. In summary, taking the iOS design to Android while respecting the Android icons would be ideal, adapted to the ecosystem and with the profile picture in the tab bar. Thank you.</p>",
