      {
        "id": 271332,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Wopfi",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/wopfi/{size}/1243_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-03T14:55:46.963Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Yadir87\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"70183\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/96bed5/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Yadir87:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I would like them to move the profile picture icon and its function to the bottom bar on Android,</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I donâ€™t think this would be a good idea. Especially because every Messenger I know has the profile picture and settings on the top left side. Why should Signal stray from this design. That would make using multiple messengers very confusing.</p>\n<p>Also, on the usability side: Why move a function that isnâ€™t used that often into the space where normally the features reside that are used every day? Especially because there isnâ€™t really any free space on the bottom bar without making it very crowded.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Yadir87\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"70183\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/96bed5/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Yadir87:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>and replace the name of the Signal app with Chats on the main screen</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Wouldnâ€™t this change make it harder to distinguish between different messengers?</p>\n<p>PS: Only a personal opinion, not a point for or against this features: I personally find the design of iOS Apps awful and unintuitive. I have to use an iPhone for work and I find it really confusing and not good looking. But as I said, only my personal opinion. Not meant to criticise iOS GUI designers.</p>",
