      {
        "id": 271354,
        "name": "Yadir",
        "username": "Yadir87",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/96bed5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-03T20:10:10.903Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Why should Signal move away from this design?</p>\n<p>The question should be; why does Signal have to be like other apps with the same purpose?</p>\n<p>Signal is characterized by being a simple, minimalist, and elegant app that makes a difference, and if I have the people I want to be in contact with on Signal, why use other messaging apps?</p>\n<p>Why move a function that is not used very often to the space where features that are used every day normally reside?</p>\n<p>The function integrated into the profile icon is not frequently used, but it is a viable possibility to reduce the header load of the app when the bottom bar only has three tabs, regardless of the visual harmony it would gain.</p>\n<p>And replace the name of the application Signal with Chats on the main screen. Wouldnâ€™t this change make it more difficult to distinguish between the different messengers?</p>\n<p>Modifying the name of the main screen to Chats is an option, just a suggestion. Personally, I prefer Android for both my personal phone and my work phone, but it is still true that on iOS the app is visually more compact, making better use of space. And although the app icons for iOS seem outdated from my perspective, there is a very noticeable difference.</p>\n<p>I respect your opinion and I equally express mine, each from their own perspective. I also do not intend to criticize the work of the graphic designers from both ecosystems; I understand that each person has their perception and I know that they cannot adjust the appâ€™s characteristics to the taste or preferences of every user. I only suggested what several of my contacts and I on Signal believe could be improved.</p>\n<p>Thank you.<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/6/8/68bd7d881374bdab847392e959994fb6c669e365.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/68bd7d881374bdab847392e959994fb6